taktsang monastery, paro taktsang monastery (tiger's nest), paro. this is one of the most important buddhist sites in the world, and guru rinpoche visited here in the 8th century on his second visit to bhutan. it is the most recognized and visited monument in bhutan. it is believed that he arrived on the back of a winged tigress, hence the name, tigers nest. the temple is built on a 1,200 meter cliff and was built in 1692. the hike up to the tiger's nest can be very strenuous and you can rent a horse to bring up the mountain for 